Plate: # the name of the plate (should be the same as the name of the directory containing the image files)
Well: # the well location e.g. A1, A2, A3, etc
Well Number: # if preferred well numbers 1 to 96 or 1 to 384 can be used instead of well locations
Analysis Gene Annotation Build: # the genome assembly and gene annotation build that the reagents were mapped to for this analysis E.g. GRCh37, Ensembl release 61, Feb 2011
Gene Annotation Comments: # any comments about the annotation e.g.  'siRNA did not map to any transcripts'
Control Type: # if the well is a control then choose from: positive control, negative control, empty well.  If it is not a control then leave blank.
Control Comments: # any additional information about the control can be entered here e.g. 'checks for transfection', 'gives strong phenotype'
Quality Control: # enter any quality control information here.  This can be 'pass/fail' or other information such as 'no cells'
Quality Control Comments: # if you used 'pass/fail' in the Quality Control column and want to give more information then enter it here
Channels: # the fluorophores and what they are labeling, e.g. Alexa 488:tubulin;Hoechst:DNA;Tritc:actin
Comments: # enter any other general information here
